  "rationale": "<p>For an exponential function of the form f(x) = a \u00b7 b<sup>x</sup>, f(0) = a. Here f(0) = 1, so a = 1. Then f(1) = b = 1/16, so f(x) = (1/16)<sup>x</sup>. Check: f(-1) = (1/16)<sup>-1</sup> = 16 \u2713; f(2) = 1/256 \u2713. Choice C is correct. Choices A, B, and D fail at least one of the table values.</p>",
